Bring a large #pot{} of salted water to a boil. Wash and dry produce.

Halve, core, and thinly slice @bell pepper{1}(halved, cored, and thinly sliced) into strips. Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2}(trimmed and thinly sliced), separating whites from greens. Dice @tomato{1}(diced into ½-inch pieces). Zest and quarter @lemon{1}(zested and quartered).

Remove sausage from casing if necessary; discard casing.

> Shrimp are fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 145°.

Heat a drizzle of @olive oil{1%tsp} in a large #pan{} over medium-high heat. Add bell pepper and scallion whites; cook, stirring, until slightly softened, ~{3-4%minutes}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Add @pork sausage{1}(removed from casing) to pan; cook, breaking up meat into pieces, until browned and cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes}.

Season with salt and pepper. If you like things spicy, stir in a pinch of @chili flakes{1%pinch} and cook until fragrant, ~{15%seconds}.

> TIP: If there's excess grease in your pan, carefully pour it out.

Rinse @shrimp{10%oz} under cold water and pat dry with #paper towels{}; season with salt and pepper. Swap in shrimp or chicken sausage for pork sausage; cook, stirring frequently (no need to break up shrimp into pieces!), until cooked through, ~{3-4%minutes} for shrimp.

Once water is boiling, add @rigatoni pasta{6%oz} to pot. Cook, stirring occasionally, until al dente, ~{9-11%minutes}.

Reserve ½ cup pasta cooking water, then drain.

Add tomato to pan with sausage mixture and cook until softened, ~{1-2%minutes}. Reduce heat to medium low.

Stir in @cream cheese{2%tbsp}, @sour cream{3%tbsp}, half the @Parmesan cheese{3%tbsp} (save the rest for serving), ¼ cup reserved pasta cooking water, and @butter{1%tbsp} until thoroughly combined.

> For 4 servings, use 1/3 cup reserved pasta cooking water and 2 TBSP butter.

Season with salt, pepper, and lemon zest to taste. Add drained rigatoni and toss to coat.

> TIP: If needed, stir in more reserved pasta cooking water a splash at a time until pasta is coated in a creamy sauce.

Divide pasta between bowls. Sprinkle with scallion greens, remaining Parmesan, and a pinch of chili flakes if desired. Serve with lemon wedges on the side.